[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     36[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206mA few things worth knowing upfront:[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     37[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     38[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe barrier classifier is the part most plans skip and the part that distinguishes a good adherence program from a reminder spam campaign.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m This example wires the rule-based classifier as the primary signal, treats the supervised classifier as a refinement, and uses the LLM as a second opinion for high-stakes cases. Production needs a structured pharmacist-consult protocol that captures barrier labels at meaningful volume; without it, the supervised classifier never learns past its rule-based baseline.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     39[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe uplift model is the second-hardest part.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Same caveat as Recipe 4.4: production-grade uplift estimation requires either a randomized hold-out arm or careful propensity-score adjustment on observational data. The training script is out of scope for this companion; the main recipe's "Why This Isn't Production-Ready" section walks through the gap.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     40[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mBedrock model IDs change over time.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Some regions require cross-region inference profile IDs (prefixed [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mus.[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m or [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140meu.[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m). The IDs below are reasonable defaults; verify in the Bedrock console for your region before running.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     41[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAll patients, fills, interventions, and engagement events in the example are synthetic.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Do not treat any specific patient_id, NDC, fill date, copay, or engagement signal as real. A production system ingests from a real PBM feed under BAA.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     42[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe example collapses Step Functions, Glue, Athena, and SageMaker Batch Transform into a single Python file for readability.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m In production these are separate workflow stages with their own error handling, IAM, and DLQs. Comments call out where the boundaries should fall.[K
